Reasoning: The paper deals with implementing distributed protocols on communication networks with adversarial errors, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves information theory concepts such as error rates and channel capacity, which suggests the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The use of communication networks and network topology suggests the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also deals with security and adversarial attacks, which suggests the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves simulations and complexity analysis, which suggests the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
